{"title_page": "List of Akron Zips head football coaches", "text_new": "{{short description|Wikimedia list article}}\n[[File:John Heisman.jpg|thumb|upright|John Heisman, namesake of the [[Heisman Trophy]] award, led Buchtel College to a 6\u20132 record in 1893\u201394.]]\nThe [[Akron Zips football]] program is a [[college football]] team that represents the [[University of Akron]] (formerly known as Buchtel College). The team has had 27 head coaches since it began playing organized football in 1891. Among those coaches, only [[Gordon K. Larson]], [[Jim Dennison]], [[J.D. Brookhart]], and current head coach [[Terry Bowden]] have led Akron to postseason appearances. Brookhart is the only coach to win a [[Athletic conference|conference]] championship with the Zips; he won the [[Mid-American Conference]] in [[2005 Akron Zips football team|2005]]. Dennison is the school's all-time leader in games won and seasons coached.\n\n==Key==\n{{List of college football program head coaches key}}\n\n==Coaches==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|+ List of head football coaches showing season(s) coached, overall records, conference records, postseason records, championships and selected awards{{#tag:ref|Statistics correct as of the end of the [[2017 NCAA Division I FBS football season|2017 college football season]].|group=\"A\"}}\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" | No.\n! scope=\"col\" | Name\n! scope=\"col\" | Season(s)\n! scope=\"col\" | GC\n! scope=\"col\" | OW\n! scope=\"col\" | OL\n! scope=\"col\" | OT\n! scope=\"col\" | O%\n! scope=\"col\" | CW\n! scope=\"col\" | CL\n! scope=\"col\" | CT\n! scope=\"col\" | C%\n! scope=\"col\" | PW\n! scope=\"col\" | PL\n! scope=\"col\" | PT\n! scope=\"col\" | DC\n! scope=\"col\" | CC\n! scope=\"col\" | NC\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" | Awards\n|-\n| {{ntsh|1}}N/A\n! scope=\"row\" | {{ntsh|0}}''No coach''{{#tag:ref|[[College Football Data Warehouse]] lists an additional loss in 1891, a forfeit to [[Denison University#Athletics|Denison]] due to inclement weather, that is not included in the University of Akron's records.<ref name=\"Akron 1890s\">{{cite web |author=Staff |year=2015 |url=http://www.cfbdatawarehouse.com/data/active/a/akron/yearly_results.php?year=1891 |title=1891-1894 Yearly Results |work=Akron Yearly Results |publisher=[[College Football Data Warehouse]] |accessdate=May 6, 2018 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150905174007/http://www.cfbdatawarehouse.com/data/active/a/akron/yearly_results.php?year=1891 |archivedate=September 5, 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"Page 158\">[[#Media Guide|2017 University of Akron Football Media Guide]], [http://www.gozips.com/documents/2017/7/24//pp_131_166_Records.pdf?id=12265 Records], p.&nbsp;158.</ref>|group=\"A\"}}\n| {{sort|1891|1891}}\n| {{nts|4}}\n| {{nts|1}}\n| {{nts|3}}\n| {{nts|0}}\n| {{nts|{{Winning percentage|1|3}}}}\n| {{ntsh|-1}}\u2014\n| {{ntsh|-1}}\u2014\n| {{ntsh|-1}}\u2014\n| {{ntsh|-1}}\u2014\n| {{ntsh|-1}}\u2014\n| {{ntsh|-1}}\u2014\n| {{ntsh|-1}}\u2014\n| {{ntsh|-1}}\u2014\n| {{ntsh|-1}}\u2014\n| {{nts|0}}\n| {{ntsh|-1}}\u2014\n|-\n| {{ntsh|2}}1\n! scope=\"row\" | {{Sortname|Frank|Cook|Frank Cook (American football)}}\n| {{sort|1892|1892}}\n| {{nts|7}}\n| {{nts|3}}\n| {{nts|4}}\n| {{nts|0}}\n| {{nts|{{Winning percentage|3|4}}}}\n| {{ntsh|-1}}\u2014\n| {{ntsh|-1}}\u2014\n| {{ntsh|-1}}\u2014\n| {{ntsh|-1}}\u2014\n| {{ntsh|-1}}\u2014\n| {{ntsh|-1}}\u2014\n| {{ntsh|-1}}\u2014\n| {{ntsh|-1}}\u2014\n| {{ntsh|-1}}\u2014\n| {{nts|0}}\n| {{ntsh|-1}}\u2014\n|-\n| {{ntsh|3}}2\n| scope=\"row\" align=\"center\" bgcolor=#FFE6BD | '''{{Sortname|John|Heisman}}'''<sup>\u2020</sup><ref name=\"Heisman\">{{cite web |author=Staff |year=2016 |url={{College Football HoF/url|id=1297}} |title=Member Biography: John Heisman |work=[[College Football Hall of Fame]] |publisher=[[National Football Foundation]] |accessdate=May 1, 2018 |url-status=dead}}</ref>\n| {{sort|1893|1893{{ndash}}94}}\n| {{nts|8}}\n| {{nts