}}\n| {{nts|75}}\n| {{nts|31}}\n| {{nts|44}}\n| {{ntsh|-1}}\u2013\n| {{nts|{{Winning percentage|31|44}}}}\n| {{nts|21}}\n| {{nts|27}}\n| {{ntsh|-1}}\u2013\n| {{nts|{{Winning percentage|21|27}}}}\n| {{nts|1}}\n| {{nts|1}}\n| {{ntsh|-1}}\u2013\n| {{nts|1}}\n| {{nts|0}}\n| {{nts|0}}\n| {{ntsh|-1}}\u2014\n|}\n\n==Notes==\n{{reflist|group=\"A\"}}\n\n==References==\n'''General'''\n{{Refbegin}}\n* {{cite web |ref=CFDW |author=Staff |year=2014 |url=http://www.cfbdatawarehouse.com/data/active/a/akron/coaching_records.php |title=Akron Coaching Records |work=Akron History |publisher=[[College Football Data Warehouse]] |accessdate=May 1, 2018 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150905180102/http://www.cfbdatawarehouse.com/data/active/a/akron/coaching_records.php |archivedate=September 5, 2015 |url-status=dead}}\n* {{cite web |ref=Media Guide |author=University of Akron Athletics Communications |year=2017 |url=https://s3.amazonaws.com/sidearm.sites/akron.sidearmsports.com/documents/2017/7/24/2017_Akron_Football_Media_Guide_sm.pdf |title=2017 University of Akron Football Media Guide |format=PDF |location=[[Akron, Ohio]] |publisher=[[University of Akron]] |accessdate=May 1, 2017 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180501214352/https://s3.amazonaws.com/sidearm.sites/akron.sidearmsports.com/documents/2017/7/24/2017_Akron_Football_Media_Guide_sm.pdf |archivedate=May 1, 2018 |url-status=live}}\n{{Refend}}\n\n'''Specific'''\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Akron Zips football coach navbox}}\n{{Akron Zips football navbox}}\n{{Mid-American Conference football coach navbox}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Akron Zips head football coaches}}\n[[Category:Lists of college football head coaches]]\n[[Category:Akron Zips football coaches|*]]\n[[Category:Ohio sports-related lists]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Wikimedia list article}}\n[[File:John Heisman.jpg|thumb|upright|John Heisman, namesake of the [[Heisman Trophy]] award, led Buchtel College to a 6\u20132 record in 1893\u201394.]]\nThe [[Akron Zips football]] program is a [[college football]] team that represents the [[University of Akron]] (formerly known as Buchtel College). The team has had 27 head coaches since it began playing organized football in 1891. Among those coaches, only [[Gordon K. Larson]], [[Jim Dennison]], [[J.D. Brookhart]], and current head coach [[Terry Bowden]] have led Akron to postseason appearances. Brookhart is the only coach to win a [[Athletic conference|conference]] championship with the Zips; he won the [[Mid-American Conference]] in [[2005 Akron Zips football team|2005]]. Dennison is the school's all-time leader in games won and seasons coached.\n\n==Key==\n{{List of college football program head coaches key}}\n\n==Coaches==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|+ List of head football coaches showing season(s) coached, overall records, conference records, postseason records, championships and selected awards{{#tag:ref|Statistics correct as of the end of the [[2017 NCAA Division I FBS football season|2017 college football season]].|group=\"A\"}}\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" | No.\n! scope=\"col\" | Name\n! scope=\"col\" | Season(s)\n! scope=\"col\" | GC\n! scope=\"col\" | OW\n! scope=\"col\" | OL\n! scope=\"col\" | OT\n! scope=\"col\" | O%\n! scope=\"col\" | CW\n! scope=\"col\" | CL\n! scope=\"col\" | CT\n! scope=\"col\" | C%\n! scope=\"col\" | PW\n! scope=\"col\" | PL\n! scope=\"col\" | PT\n! scope=\"col\" | DC\n! scope=\"col\" | CC\n! scope=\"col\" | NC\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" | Awards\n|-\n| {{ntsh|1}}N/A\n! scope=\"row\" | {{ntsh|0}}''No coach''{{#tag:ref|[[College Football Data Warehouse]] lists an additional loss in 1891, a forfeit to [[Denison University#Athletics|Denison]] due to inclement weather, that is not included in the University of Akron's records.<ref name=\"Akron 1890s\">{{cite web |author=Staff |year=2015 |url=http://www.cfbdatawarehouse.com/data/active/a/akron/yearly_results.php?year=1891 |title=1891-1894 Yearly 